description: A squad of Vicious Circle agents, including DoubleHeader, invade the Police Headquarters Dragon and Cyberface are in. Frank Darling also returns and aids the Dragon and the Police in defeating agents, even though Captain Stewart is killed. Cyberface agrees to testify against Overlord in return for his freedom, and a SWAT team including the Dragon confronts Overlord in his highrise headquarters.

The Violator waits below in the sewer system, preparing to deliver a message to his nemesis, one that won't soon be forgotten.

While this is going on Spawn warns his fellow bums that it is no longer safe to be around him, however Bobby reacts by telling him no matter what kind of freaks have shown up recently it's nothing different from the challenges they face every day.

Meanwhile Sam visits Twitch in the hospital, and though it appears Twitch has been badly broken, Sam realizes that Twitch feels a lot better than he looks, especially when his 7 kids come and visit him.

Finally Spawn makes his way to the sewer where an all out battle between him, and the violator break out. The violator curses Spawn, telling him what an honor it is to be chosen a hell spawn. Eventually the fight is put on hold when a water line explodes, sending our warriors literally up sh!ts creek.
name: Shadows

description:
Notes:

  • "Dedicated to Melinda Gebbie The Champ Vamp"
  • Additional thanks to Electric Pickle and Philip Timper.
  • "End Cap" two pages featuring McFarlane Toys.
name: Blood Feud Part 2
Gods of War

description: Loki sends an ice giant to Earth and attack. Prototype is the first to arrive and fight the beast, but realizes he needs assistance and calls in Ultraforce. The ice giant escapes and Black Knight tries to search for answers. He learns that Loki is behind the assault and wonders how he can stop him. He tries to contact his former teammates in the Avengers through mystical means but is unable to speak to anyone. Sersi suddenly arrives and attacks, being possessed by an INfinity Gem. Loki, meanwhile, looks over the ultras on the planet to divine where the Infinity Gems are so he can use them to destroy the Avengers.
name: The Iceman Cometh

description: The island the Avengers have been fighting on deteriorates into an illusion of A.I.M. M.O.D.O.K. makes an ill-fated attempt to save reality, but time is not on his side. Witness the Super-Adaptoid make the ultimate sacrifice!
name: Taking A.I.M. (Part 4 of 4)

description: M.O.D.O.K. is back with a vengeance! Witness as Captain America battles both villains and heroes as his fight against A.I.M. continues!
name: Through the Perilous Fight
Into The Vault Of Dreams
Malignancy

description:
Chamber is hanging out in his basement lair trying to get the TV to work. Gateway suddenly appears and the two have a telepathic conversation. Gateway tells Chamber that Paige is upset about the Legacy Virus and needs a friend to talk to and he Chamber to be that friend.

Meanwhile, the other Generation X kids (Jubilee, Skin, M, and Synch) are in New York City. Jubilee buys some apples from Penance but her apples are ruined when a mob chases Thing down the street because they love Fantastic Four. The Generation X kids do some New York City tourist stuff like visit Rockefeller Center. While they are there M has a spell of some sort and spaces out becoming completely immobile and an unsavory looking character appears and talks to Skin, expressing surprise to see him alive.

Back at the school, Banshee is trying to get Penance to talk by using random language books to see if she might understand a language other than English. After speaking to her in French for a bit, he calls it a day and heads back to his on-campus housing thinking about how why he is trying so hard to talk to Penance and whether or not it's so he doesn't have to talk to Moira who recently became the first human to be infected with the Legacy Virus. He gets to his house to find that Penance has already gotten there and is sitting on top of his refrigerator.

Back in New York, Jubilee, Synch, and Skin have left M behind in a catatonic state and are in a car en route to Frost Enterprises to pick up Emma Frost. As they pull into the parking garage of Frost Enterprises something suddenly kills their driver and the security guards in the parking garage. The three kids get into their Generation X costumes, ready for a fight.

Back at the school Paige is hammered. She is completely drunk after drinking one beer. Chamber finds her crawling around on a pool table complaining about how life is unfair because of the Legacy Virus and how they'll all die anyway.

The Generation X kids take the elevator up into the Frost Enterprises building and are attacked by a monstrous mutant who calls himself Hemingway. Generation X makes short work of Hemingway, but he manages to escape, leaving behind the Morlock named Artie. Jubilee talks to him and tells him that they need to go and find their friends.
name: Don't Touch That Dial!

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The beloved teen teleporter Clarice Fergueson died as Blink combatting the foes of Generation X and the X-Men. In this imaginary story, the idea of Blink not getting killed puts more fated questions in mind as the In-Betweener intervenes in battling the heroes and the Marvel existence itself.
name: What  if Blink of Generation X had Not Died?
The Man Who Fell to Earth

description: Reprints from Marvel Superheroes (2nd series) #377-383
name: The Return of Captain Britain

description:
The complete archives are available if you visit http://www.elfquest.com/gallery/OnlineComics3.html.

The Wolfriders are training in order to keep their skills sharp. The whole family bathes naked together. Skywise becomes even more of a nuisance, and Ember decides to take sword training from Nightfall.

Teir joins in with the games and sports, and displays his precision and strength, even challenging Skywise to a duel. Skywise wins but presses Teir how he learned swordsmanship. Teir is not comfortable sharing any information, and the wolf-pack reacts to the emotional tention.

Diplomatically, this further ostracizes both characters. Skywise feels less and less useful, and by rejecting Teir, Teir backs off and becomes more shadowy, less trustful. It was a good reason why Skywise left Ember's part of the Wolfriders and find Cutter and Aroree in ElfQuest: Hidden Years #26.
name: INHERITANCE

description:
In this issue, First Born Of The Neverending and Jink are locked into a "sending", exchanging the story of their mutual origins. It turns out that the planetary fore runners were once united by the first world The High-Ones' initial departure.

The elves' path of devolution appear to be much nicer than the Neverending's, who have faced racial wars, pitted against armies of robots, emerging triumphant though in greatly diminished numbers.

Tribal Reunification with the Neverending

This is the episode where the shard from the Palace is joined to the shard from the Neverending, thus is yet another bold exemplification of the vastness of Cutter's goal of total Tribal Reunification. Jink tells the Firstborn "LET OUR MINDS STAY TOGETHER -- WE'LL UNDERSTAND EACH OTHER BETTER."
name: SHOULD AULD ACQUAINTENCE

description: After rummaging through the Murderworld wreckage, Cable and Domino head out to find an old friend, Blaquesmith. He had been attacked by someone looking for information on Cable. Cable returns to X-Force with yet another worry.
name: "...Our Regularly Scheduled Program..."

description: The Guardians decide to take the fight to the past to destroy the Badoon invasion that had caused so much trouble. Talon is left behind in the present as a liability.
name: Endgame

person_credits.name: David Mack
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description:
Doctor Strange is still looking after Sister Nil who wants to walk among the humans but Strange fears this. After a small argument, Strange goes to sleep.

Strange is roaming in a field as a dog and Sister Nil is running a side of him. All of a sudden they get attacked by a green wolf which turns out to be Nightmare. Doctor tries to ward off Nightmare but Nightmare kidnapes Sister Nil.

Nightmare tries to use Sister Nil at his own advantage but Strane takes her away but Nightmare ends u fighting Strange. In the end Strange badly burns Nightmare nearly killing him. NIghtmare then tells Strange he wants his to run the NIghtmare Realm. Nightmare then goes on a burning boat to die off but Strange would not alowe it. He saves Nightmare from the burning boat and him and Sister NIl Leave the dream world.
name: Farewell Nightmare Music

description:
Who stopped the Juggernaut?

Archangel is contacted by Charlotte Jones in response to a hate crime, mutant on human. Meanwhile, after a movie, Beast and Bishop witness Juggernaut fall from the sky. They, and later Psylocke, investigate and find a now-stoppable Juggernaut. He's frenzied and warns the X-Men of a being that could throw him from Canada to New Jersey: Onslaught.
name: Dark Walk

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Green Lantern guest-stars as Aquaman and the emerald warrior clash on an explosive environmental issue. Meanwhile, things are coming apart in Atlantis as the city's monarch dies...and the Atlanteans can turn to only one person to hold their underwater world together!

The Old One is dying and the various fish of the ocean are worked up trying to get a message to Aquaman,which is eventually delivered by a dolphin. While two divers attack a shark which injures a diver in self defense before being severely hurt. Seeing this on the news Kyle Rayner decides to help the people rid the shark instead of focusing on the galactic problems which so often call his attention. King Thesily continues his growing hatred of the people's growing approval of Koryak and his father fearing his loss of his throne,deciding to be first in the people's hearts or die trying.

Green Lantern then reaches Crescent falls beach agreeing to kill the shark for the mayor, he then descends into the water preparing to shoot a shark he has seen with a harpoon gun construct only to be prevented by Aquaman. Aquaman then tells Rayenr the shark is off limits because it's dying and once it is dead it will be eaten by another, and that he spared the humans life before insulting him for not being the true Green Lantern which causes Kyle to decide to kill the shark. The two then commence in a battle before Green Lantern is attacked by a shark coming to Aquaman's aid. Aquaman then utilizes his grappling hook to steal the ring, but gives it back with a compliment and urging him to have the compassion his predecessor once had before leaving to talk with the old one for his message, which he has forgotten.

Back in Poseidonis Theisly begins his plan calling Koryak away and lures him into a deserted hall to murder him with a hidden dagger but is stopped by another earthquake.Following the earthquake Thesily attacks Koryak, but is disarmed and crushed by falling debris.
name: Revelations

description: Werewolf 3, like a Scooby-Doo story, the werewolf turns out to be a fake; Batman captures the killer.
name: Werewolf Part 3 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
The X-Men share their concerns about teammate-gone-rogue Wolverine. Will his fellow mutants be able to pull Logan back from the edge? Or will the man be lost and become fully feral?

After his mortal confrontation with Sabretooth last issue, Wolverine retreats to the wilderness of his own accord, sighting his increasingly savage nature. The X-Men attempt to make Wolverine change his mind, but an ominous question lingers in the air; who is the true animal? Logan, or mankind?
name: Path Of Stones, Wood Of Thorns

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Overview

Lewis Polk is a good cop. But in a bad town, a good cop is the worst thing you can be. When Polk sticks his too-clean nose into the wrong kind of business once too often, he finds Hunter Rose, the original Grendel, all too happy to cut it off. And Rose won't stop cutting there; his wounds tend to run deeper than that.

Reprinting issues 16 and 17 of the color Grendel series initially published in 1988, Grendel Classics #1 brings back into print this highly demanded story of the original Grendel, Hunter Rose, with a new format and new cover by Grendel creator Matt Wagner. Wagner utilizes a bold and experimental style for this Chandler-esque character study, exploring one man's struggle to uncover the truth in a corrupt world -- the world of Grendel!
name: Devil Eyes
The Torch Is Passed (Atlantis Rising, Part)
Return On The Warlord

description: The Headhunter and his super-powered entourage descend on Arcadia. They've heard tales of the mysterious X, and they're looking for a little blood sport. And though he's only one man, he's proven himself more than a man, and more than capable of handling this pack of amateurs. Until, that is, a woman from his past pops up out of nowhere, revealing secrets that shouldn't be told. How do you protect a city when you're busy trying to protect your own past? Find out in this issue ofX!
name: Past Masters

description: The Year One Annuals continue, exploring pivotal events and untold stories of the DC Universe's greatest heroes. Four stories integral to Aquaman's past revolve around the villain Triton, son of Poseidon. Superman guest-stars as Triton unleashes his fury against the Sea King; Aquaman must aid a young Princess Diana when the Wonder-Woman-to-be is "chosen" by Triton; Arthur Curry takes Mera to her first encounter with air breathers and...champagne; and when Aquaman's first son is born, the god Poseidon shows Aquaman who's really King of the Seas.
name: Year One

description:
Catwoman's existence becomes miserable when she suddenly finds herself unable to pull a job that the cops have not known about or that someone else has not gotten to first. Feels like someone is watching every move she makes. It has something to do with the Marquez dagger she stole six months ago, dagger that has been in the Marquez family for centuries. And the Marquez family is the world's second most powerful drug cartel.

Catwoman sets out to South America to try and solve the problem...
name: Family Ties

description: Seen through the eyes of his beguilingly amoral companion, this seductive psychological drama explores the turbulent life of Leonardo da Vinci in shockingly intimate detail.
name: Book One: Greater than Light

description: In this Maximum Clonage prologue, learn why everybody hates clones!
name: Everyone hates a clone

description:
Bloodaxe is back at work disrupting the work of criminals and trying to locate Seth. Bloodaxe is beginning to feel that working with Masterson (Thunderstrike) may be possible in the future.

Masterson is reeling from a recent stalemate in a battle with Seth. He has been marked by Seth for death. Eric's personal life gets even more complicated as Booby Steele wants to make amends with him and Jackie Lukus wants to move forward with a more intimate relationship. Eric search for Bloodaxe is going nowhere, at one time he suspected Bobby Steele. He then begins to trail Gary Paretsky who is acting funny only to run into Susan Austin and Ed Marrero who are also acting suspiciously.

Nearby, Jerry Sapristi is attacked by Mongoose and Quicksand who have staked out the construction site where Masterson often works. Bloodaxe arrives first on the scene and save Jerry. Bloodaxe would have killed Mongoose if not for Thunderstrike's interference. Mongoose is defeated by Thunderstrike and Quicksand is defeated by Bloodaxe. Bloodaxe is defeated and revealed to be Jackie Lukus. Thunderstrike takes the executioner's axe and goes after Seth.
name: Bloodaxe: Unmasked
Falls Upon Anarky: Part One: Prophet of Doom

description: The Sovereign Seven arrive on Earth, on the run from The Rapture, and end up in a fight with the Female Furies.
name: It Was A Dark and Stormy Night...

description: Anima and her friends have brought the aged Liv to the hospital, where they watch over her. While her friends whether or not to decide to let her die since she has H.I.V., Liv still exists as a ghost in the Arkana. Two Archai try to advise Liv, while the Granny Killer hunts her. Liv and the Granny Killer are connected through this umbilical cord through the Arkana, and the Granny Killer tracks her down. Meanwhile, both Agent Woodleaf and Animus aids Anima to also track down Liv. Anima confronts the Granny Killer, who tries to absorb her life just like Liv. But the Granny Killer ends up absorbing Animus energies instead, which cause the Granny Killer to de-age himself to an embryo. Liv returns to her rightful age. In the end, Anima accepts a position with the O.D.D. with Agent Woodleaf, and leaves the group.
name: Love Will Tear Us Apart Again

description:
Andromeda will die within a day unless Brainiac 5 can develop a serum to counter her lead poisoning. Plus, the Legion's partnership with the United Planets begins to disintegrate when one Legionnaire is unmasked as a traitor.

Brainiac 5 works on a cure for Andromeda's lead poisoning while she reconsiders her racist views, and Shrinking Violet makes a startling discovery.
name: "Beyond Belief".

description:
In the wake of "The Death of Clark Kent," the mysterious Shadowdragon tries to aid Superman in returning to Metropolis--but that may not be an option.

As Conduit makes his last stand, Superman goes on the offensive!

Notes:

  • Kryptonian based energy used by Conduit on Superman.
  • Triangle 1995 #25.
  • Chronological continuation from Action Comics #711.
  • Chronological continuation in Superman #102.
name: Finish Line!

description:
Nazi werewolves plan to detonate a nuclear device in New York and bring the world to its knees! The Eternal Warrior must locate and disarm the bombs before it is too late. Can he save this world or will another be rebuilt from the ashes?

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".

1st appearance:

- Fenris (Fenris League)
name: Lest Darkness Fall

description: Magnus and company discover that the freewill robots have not been destroyed; they are very much alive in The Invisible Legion Part Two.
name: The Invisible Legion - Part Two

description: Now back in the Lost Land which is threatened by an evil force commanded by the Campaigner, Turok and company are surprised to find an ally in their battle their old enemy Captain Red.
name: The Prodigal - Part 3: New Unities
Genesis Denied, Part One

description:
As Vido shows up to look at the mess Luse made in #1, Luse is offered a job with Sanctuary on two conditions.

1. Kill Ghost
2. Make Sanctuaries top assassin, Cassy, submit.

or

Be killed.

name: Eno and Plum; The Artistic Impulse; The Secret Life of Leftovers; Pistachio!!; The Ninth Gland; The Chained Coffin

description: In Rio, Rosie gets directions about her powers from a levitating vision named Jenny as Agent Hooks, Constable Dixon and the Butcher Bruvvers close in for the kill.
name: On A Hot Summer's Night

description:
Gilad recounts the earliest adventure of his millenia long immortal life. But though the young warrior discovers he can survive neary any wound, will he be able to protect his people from the ravages of the Spider Aliens and their Queen Mother?

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".
name: Childhood's End - Part One

volume.name: Ice Age on the World of Magic: The Gathering

description: A robot invasion starts and these robots are not freewills nor Malevs but something new that Magnus and company have to deal with in Return of the Robots Part One.
name: Return Of The Robots - Part One
Brave New World - Part II

description: Wanting revenge for the destruction of his people and their village, Captain Red decides to take the fight for the Lost Land right straight to the Campaigner and Turok and company go with him.
name: The Prodigal - Part 4: Stronghold

1. Fallen Flanders (Flanders gone bad!)
  2. The Kwik-E and the Dead! (Homer vs Mr. Burns in the 1800's)
  3. Homer Simpson
name: Fallen Flanders

description: Kei and Yuri, The Dirty Pair, have leveled cities, slaughtered armadas, and even destroyed whole planets, all in the line of duty! Now the dastardly Kevin Sleet launches his secret weapon against the destructive duo . . . a psychotic clone of Yuri! If two members of The Dirty Pair can lay waste to entire worlds, what's going to happen with three?

volume.name: The Dirty Pair: Fatal But Not Serious

description:
The Stories in the first part of the 100th issue contain:

Lance Blastoff by Frank Miller

Hartbreakers by Anina Bennett and Paul Guinan

Peeling and Eating a Tangerine by Harvey Pekar

The Ninth Gland by Renee French

Aboard the Drinking Leviathan by Jon Lewis

Milk and Cheese by Evan Dorkin

and a pin up of Mimi Rodin by Dave Stevens

When Rogue Squadron leader Wedge Antilles is downed in a bloody battle against Imperial All Terrain Scout Transports, he is forced to form an uneasy alliance with the Cilpari natives, whose dislike for the Rebels is only dwarfed by their hatred for the Empire. Wedge must regroup Rogue Squadron before the Cilpari alliance is shattered, and rejoin the battle to save the galaxy!
name: The Rebel Opposition, Chapter 2

description:
Superman in prison! The Man of Steel referees a boxing match between Bloodsport I and Bloodsport II.

Notes:

  • Both Bloodsports (Robert DuBois and Alex Trent) appear in this story.
  • A modified version of the Toastmaster appears. It was the size of a pistol but still maintained the power of the original Toastmaster.
  • On page 13 panel 2 Lois made the comment, "I ever tell you how 'Mooch' Carlin had a crush on me?" This is a joke aimed at editor Mike Carlin who was credited as "Mooch" Carlin in the story credits.
  • Triangle 1995 #32.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #103.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #713.
name: Title Bout!

location_credits.name: Stryker's Island Maximum Security Internment Center

description: Part 2 of the 3-part 'Anima Mundi': Animal Man's trip to the Hollow Earth becomes an hallucinatory nightmare.
name: The Princess, The Shaman King, and The Spider Queen
Light In Dark, Patr 4 - TV Or Not TV

description:
Azrael at last learns the secrets behind the System and his hidden heritage. Plus, Sister Lilhy makes a startling self-discovery, leading to an equally startling transformation!

Azrael reached his destination and learned of the Azrael breeding process. He had been ripped from his mother's womb, incubated, combined with ancient beasts, and tortured in order to be Azrael
name: Fallen Angel 7: The Curse

description:
Killer Croc escapes Arkham Asylum and the trail leads Batman to Louisiana, where Croc's mysterious ally awaits!

Killer Croc's insanity grows while he is locked away in Arkham Asylum. Croc manages to escape and heads south, with Batman chasing after him.

Alfred returns to the Wayne Mansion. James Gordon becomes a candidate for Mayor of Gotham.
name: Killer Croc: Fast Train to the Wet Dark

description:
Part 1 of the 5-part 'Playgrounds.' Mr. Wrong and Barbatos the demon return to divert Tim's guardian angels.

Sir Timothy, now knowingly on the down and outs, tries to pawn minor magic items with little success. He almost starts a job and a new leaf though, but Barbatos manages to persuade him to stay indigent and self-indulgent.

Young Tim takes Molly to the abandoned lot where he played as a child, and introduces her to his magical creations. They enjoy talking to Tanger and Crimple, who both warm up to the new human.

Khara and Nikki take in a show in America. On the way home, they are hunted by demons in the shape of dumb pink T. rexes. The ladies almost get away by turning into garbage cans, but Barbatos smells out their disguises.

Molly has to go to the bathroom, and is afraid to be alone in the thicket after hearing of the scarier creatures Tim once created.

We learn that Barbatos has been successful in playing his control over Sir Timothy in the continual competition for prominence among demons.

Crimple goes with Molly so she won't be alone, bravely leaving his tree for the first time. Tim and Tanger eventually follow to help.

Araquel, still chained above the Pit, sees Nikki, who tells him that Khara was captured. Nikki almost falls in the Pit, but Araquel breaks his chains and saves her--only to find that she's really Barbatos, and that he has now forsaken his heavenly-mandated punishment.
name: Playgrounds, Part I: Hell And Back

description: Part 3 of the 3-part 'Picking Up the Pieces.' J'onn J'onzz, the Martian Manhunter, tries to rescue Damage from Vandal Savage.
name: Ties That Bind

description: Monarch's secret agenda is revealedand the answer may change Captain Atom's life forever!
name: The Once and Future Monarch

description: Zatanna makes her long-awaited return to the stage while Jared enjoys the show-but the Firebringers interrupt with a show-stopping admission of guilt.
name: Dance on Fire!

description: Wally and Linda investigate a case involving Linda's ex-husband and some demons. Meanwhile, Mirror Master lurks.
name: The Quickening

description:
"The Siege of Zi Charam" part 2, continued from NEW TEEN TITANS (1984-1988) #120. Can even the combined might of Supergirl and Green Lantern rescue the New Titans from the clutches of the deadly Progenitors? Continued in DARKSTARS (1992-1996) #34.

Kyle is floating in space and Supergirl (the Matrix version) saves him and they board a nearby ship after dismantling its weaponry. Donna tries to calm down Minion telling him to allow the duo to handle things. He is hotheaded so he heads off in their direction while Donna chides herself for not being able to calm him.

On the ship the duo takes on the aliens inside while Minion fights to get to the ship. Donna is not sure what to do, assist him or follow with her plan. Matrix uses her shapshiftting to impersonate the aliens and bring in Kyle as a prisoner. They manage to infiltrate the ship and make their way to the holding cells where they rescue the captured team. Donna gets on board and they free some other aliens. Arsenal argues with Donna about not being able to handle the situation. Minion arrives badly injured and reveals to the team hes been tracked by every ship the invaders have.
name: Rescue: The Siege of the Zi Charam, Part 2

description: "Critical Mass" part 1! As John Constantine wrestles with a dark memory, a demon with an appetite for children's souls hatches an ambitious plot to realign the balance of power in hell.
name: Critical Mass, Part 1: Bait

description: Bart faces repercussions from his involvement with White Lightning's gang, but when Lightning strikes again, this time at the Minhota Casino, Bart must not only save the lives of innocent civilians, but the life of the super-villainess as well!
name: Lightning Strikes

description:
In this issue illustrated by John Ridgway (HELLBLAZER), a new breed of upper-class hunters with a strange connection to the Invisibles is loose on the London Streets, preying upon the homeless

A servant in Glamis Castle pushes a meal trolley towards a solitary room as he has done three times a day for the past six years. On the trolley is a platter. On the platter is a human carcass. In the room is a giant mirror. The servant flashes a prism in front of the mirror using five unique gestures. The mirror ripples... and a hideous tentacle-faced monster steps out. From the other side of the mirror is an unearthly cacophony of horrible noise. The monster goes to the carcass and spews out a dissolving foam. It then drags the mutilated corpse through the mirror with it. As it does so, the monster glances back at the servant. The servant feels that the monster is beginning to like him.

Sir Miles Delacourt and his assistant Tarquin are riding in a limousine through the country. They are being followed by a red box truck. Sir Miles bitterly tells Tarquin that he would like nothing more to torture King Mob, especially after the recent debacles at Harmony House and with Orlando. The two vehicles stop at a small cul-de-sac in the woods. Tarquin and Sir Miles go over to the box truck which is full of homeless people. As the homeless people are shepherded out, Sir Miles remarks that he is looking forward to reducing the country's poverty level.

After a brief interlude that explains the historical significance of Glamis Castle, we return to Sir Miles who is chatting with another man at the aforementioned castle. Tarquin is playing with a gun while they talk, admiring the quality. Sir Miles tells Willie about their recent troubles with Diana and her inability to produce a suitable moonchild to inherit the throne. Sir Miles is not that worried however, they do have another moonchild. A butler enters bearing some port; Tarquin accidentally shoots him. Sir Miles yells at his assistant for soiling the carpet.

The servant feeds the monster another carcass. The servant is revealed to be an Invisible very deep undercover. He is supposed to kill the hideous moonchild, but he cannot bring himself to do it. He thinks it likes him.

Sir Miles is enjoying his sport of racing through the countryside hunting and killing the homeless people.

Later, the servant (whose name is Jeremy Sutton) goes down to the dungeon and talks to another servant named Des who is reading a horror novel written by an author named Kirk Morrison. One of the captive homeless people yells to be let out. Sutton looks at him and apologizes, and in the cell he is surprised to find his estranged daughter, Kate. Sutton is in shock, not least of all over Kate's hair which is pink and spikey (she is the homeless girl that Dane was talking to back in issue 2).

That night, Sir Miles reads Sutton's diary. It turns out that the Outer Church suspected that he might be an Invisible and had been watching him for the last four months. Sir Miles reads of Sutton's plan to rescue his daughter the next day, and declares that the the man must have a martyr complex. He throws the diary into the fireplace and tells Willie and Tarquin that they will give Sutton what he wants. Tarquin grins merrily.

In one of two concurrent scenes we see a guard letting the homeless people out into the woods and telling that that they had better run. He shoots a man that asks him question. In the other scene, Sir Miles and his compatriots dressed in hunting gear, let the moonchild out of his mirror realm. Tarquin is disgusted, but Sir Miles proudly informs him that this monstrosity is the future king.

The homeless people run through the woods trying to avoid being eaten by the moonchild. Sutton calls out Kate's name, and she runs to her father. They embrace, and then try to make their escape. Sutton tries to convince her to cross a tree log that spans a river, but Kate is frightened by the moonchild who is waiting on the other side. Sutton tells her not to worry, after all the creature likes him. Before she can cross, Sir Miles and his cronies approach from behind. Sutton cries out, but it is revealed that Kate has been working with Sir Miles this whole time. Sir Miles tells Sutton that it's time for his big scene. He will betray the Invisibles and tell the Outer Church everything he knows... or Tarquin will blow his daughter's head off. The servant quietly agrees that he'll talk, to no great surprise to Sir Miles. Tarquin kills Kate anyway, Sutton cries out in anguish. Sir Miles tells the man that he has no information worth anything to them anyways, he just wanted to prove to Sutton how pathetic he was.

Later, we see another servant pushing a trolley to the darkened room. This time the servant is Des. He lifts the lid covering the platter, to unveil Sutton who is to be the creature's next meal. Sutton tells Des that he's not worried... after all, he thinks the creature likes him.
name: Royal Monsters

description: Part 5 of the 7-part 'The Way of the Warrior,' continued from Guy Gardner Warrior (1992) #33. Captured by aliens, the Justice League must battle its way to freedom. Continues in Hawkman (1993 3rd Series) #23.
name: Breakout!

description:
In part 1 of the 3-part ''Naked City,'' Jesse, Tulip and Cassidy arrive in New York City, where a bizarre friend of Cassidy's may provide a clue to the whereabouts of God. NYC is also the home of a cop who wants to know more about the supernaturally powered preacher.

Jesse, Tulip and Cassidy go to New York City to get away from the law and to find some leads; the hunt is on in NYC for the Reaver-Cleaver, a vicious serial killer; Jesse works out the ethics of his Gift.
name: Say A Prayer For Seven Bullets (Naked City Part 1)

description: Ulysses Hadrian Armstrong, self styled boy general, was released from his youth detention center. He found a homeless man who thought he was Julius Caesar to front for him. Robin tracked them after they stole a lion. He fell into their trap and had to face the lion.
name: War Gods in the 'Hood

description: A new vigilante moves in on the Golden Age Sandman's turf - Rex Tyler, the Man of the Hour.
name: The Hourman: Act I of IV

description:
"The Wake" part 1! The shocking conclusion of the previous arc has altered forever the face of the Dreaming, bringing with it a time of reflection and a sad celebration. It's a wake in which friends and loved ones, relatives and rivals, fleeting lovers and immortal enemies gather to pay their respects and to mourn their loss.

The startling conclusion of the Kindly Ones brings a time of inner reflection and sad celebration. It's a wake in which those with past rivalries gather for the Wake.

The funeral service of Morpheus starts.
name: The Wake, Chapter 1: Which Occurs in the Wake of What Has Gone Before

description: Part 4 of the 5-part 'Nasty Infections.' Shade battles the Grotesque as the Changing Man attempts to free his friends from a mysterious virus.
name: Nasty Infections, Part Four: Heart Attacks

description: Star-Crossed, Part 2 of 3. Before taking command of the Starship Enterprise, Kirk visits Carol Marcus and is shocked to meet their infant son.
name: Star-Crossed Part 2 - Loved Not Wisely...

description: Part 4 of 5. A new Tholian war with the Federation seems inevitable - and the Klingons are poised to make matters even more complicated.
name: War and Madness Part IV: Ceremony of Innocence

description:
Starman learns that another of his father's enemies has returned: Solomon Grundy. Meanwhile, Nash, out for revenge upon the Knight family, takes on the identity of the Mist like her father before her. Plus, Jack has a surprisingly candid chat with The Shade...

After a conversation with The Shade, Jack pays a visit to Charity and runs into Sadie Falk - again.

Later, Jack gets a phone call from Jenny-Lyn Hayden-Scott, Jack goes in search of Solomon Grundy.

Meanwhile, Ted Knight studies Mikaal Tomas.

Elsewhere, Nash furthers her plan of revenge against Jack...
name: The Day Before the Day to Come

description: The local mob maneuvers Superboy into a super-human prizefight with Champion to prove once and for all who the true Teen of Steel is.
name: Battle of the Century

description:
The story of Anna, who has led Swamp Thing into a dizzying journey through alternative worlds, is revealed in the penultimate chapter of 'River Run.'

In the sixth story of River Run, Sink of Swim, the origin of Anna, Swamp Thing's ghostly damsel-in-distress, is revealed.

Anna had an okay life. She made a living writing comic books, plenty of money, and a hot boyfriend who did all her cooking and cleaning. That was all until she received a chain letter in the mail. When she ignores it, that's when her bad luck starts. Her publishers go bankrupt, her bank accounts are wiped clean, her boyfriend disappears in the bathtub, her house gets flooded, and she's pregnant. When she moves in with her sister and gets an abortion, Anna's horrified when her hand turns into water. At the same time, her sister get's run down by a hit-and-run driver. Left all alone, Anna has nothing left but to finish her book, River Run, but after too many expired deadlines no in interested anymore. So, she tries to kill herself with an overdose, but she uses allergy medicine by mistake. On her second attempt, she swallows a cup filled with a dozen different types of household cleaning chemicals. That does the trick.

With both Anna and Swamp Thing done with the last story, Anna dissolves into water that gets sucked into a sewer grate. Swamp Thing picks up her book, and discovers a seventh story. Anna and the Parliament of Waves.
name: Sink or Swim: Chapter Six of River Run
